Here's how you can solve it using algebra:

Expanding $(3x-2)(4x+1)$ and $(3x-2)4x+1$:
\begin{align*}
(3x-2)(4x+1) &= 12x^2 - x \\
(3x-2)4x+1 &= 12x^2 - 8x \\
\end{align*}
Substituting $x=4$ into both expressions and simplifying:
\begin{align*}
(3(4)-2)(4(4)+1) &= 56(16)-(4) \\
(3(4)-2)4(4)+1 &= 56(16)-32 \\
\end{align*}
Both simplified expressions have the same value: $\boxed{-128}$. The answer is: -128.
